libppdk -- light-wight user I/O driver for Marvell Packet Processor

---------------------------------------------------

libppdk is a light-weight user I/O driver for Marvell Packet Processor.
The purpose of this driver library is to create a wrapper for the
native implementation of Open Data Plane for Armada 8K Packet Processor.

Coding style:
Linux Kernel Coding Style
https://www.kernel.org/doc/Documentation/CodingStyle

checkpatch.pl that can be used to test for
adhering to the coding style rule.

i.e.
./checkpatch.pl -f --no-tree ../../libs/libppdk/apps/pp_app.c

Steps to build and run the PPDK library:

1. Built the UIO kernel module and install the UIO headers

> cd <your_path>/armada-ppdk/modules/uio
> export LDFLAGS=""
> make -C <path_to_kernel_source> M=$PWD
> DESTDIR=~/target/sdk make dev_install

2. Build the UIO library and install it

> cd <your_path>/armada-ppdk/libs/libuio-0.2.1
> ./autogen.sh
> ./configure --host=aarch64-poky-linux
> make -j8
> DESTDIR=~/target/sdk make install

3. Build the PPDK and install it
> cd <your_path/armada-ppdk/libs/libppdk
> ./autogen.sh
> ./configure --host=aarch64-poky-linux
> make -j8
> DESTDIR=~/target/sdk make install

4. For running PPDK apps, insert <mv_pp_uio.ko> in a
running kernel and run the application

ppdk_generator - spawns 2 x generator threads on 2 x interfaces
ppdk_rx_test   - spawns 1 x receiver thread on 1 interface
ppdx_tx_test   - spawns 1 x generator thread on 1 x interface
ppdk_swf       - validates packet correctness by spawning
                 1 x generator thread and 1 x receiver thread
                 on 1 x interface configured in loopback
ppdk_bm_test   - validates bm implementation
ppdk_cma_test  - validates cma implementation

NOTE: See PPDK.txt for PPDK functional layout by source files
NOTE: At this stage, the PPDK functions with slowpath kernel driver
      disabled
